==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cabling
<hw>Ca"bling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>The decoration of a fluted shaft of a column or of a pilaster with
reeds, or rounded moldings, which seem to be laid in the hollows of the
fluting. These are limited in length to about one third of the height of
the shaft.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cabman</ent>⟦br⟧
